properties.name: script
properties.value:
import fr.openage.ui.rule.IChoice
//CHC Todo client / Statut completion

public getChoices() {
    def key = context.current.COMPLETION.value?.toString()
	if (key==null) key='standby'

    choice0 = [
        isSelected: {'standby' == key},
        getValue: { 'En standby' },
        getKey: { 'standby' },
    ]
    choice1 = [
        isSelected: {'waiting' == key},
        getValue: { 'Attente réponse' },
        getKey: { 'waiting' },
    ]
    choice2 = [
        isSelected: {'done' == key},
        getValue: { 'Terminé' },
        getKey: { 'done' },
    ]
    choice3 = [
        isSelected: {'abandonned' == key},
        getValue: { 'Abandonné' },
        getKey: { 'abandonned' },
    ]


    return [choice0 as IChoice, choice1 as IChoice, choice2 as IChoice, choice3 as IChoice]
    
}

fields.name: ui.rules.UIWhereLabel
fields.label: Filter values
fields.description:
This rule is available if there is a relationship with a parameter table. It can filter values available in the parameter table.
One or more filters can be defined. Each filter requires a column in the table. The contents of this column activate a value in the parameter table.
Therefore, it is necessary to define as many filters as there are values that can appear in the list.
